<doc>
  <member name="D3D11_BUFFER_UAV">
    <summary>
      <para>Describes the elements in a buffer to use in a unordered-access view.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This structure is used by a <see cref="D3D11_UNORDERED_ACCESS_VIEW_DESC" />.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d11/d3d11-graphics-reference-resource-structures">Resource Structures</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_BUFFER_UAV.FirstElement">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/WinProg/windows-data-types">UINT</a></b></para>
      <para>The zero-based index of the first element to be accessed.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_BUFFER_UAV.NumElements">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/WinProg/windows-data-types">UINT</a></b></para>
      <para>The number of elements in the resource. For structured buffers, this is the number of structures in the buffer.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_BUFFER_UAV.Flags">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/WinProg/windows-data-types">UINT</a></b></para>
      <para>View options for the resource (see <see cref="D3D11_BUFFER_UAV_FLAG" />).</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>